column4: ok folks...I don't have electricsheep installed and I downloaded deb file for the new electricsheep 2.6 and did sudo dpkg -i electricsheep_2.6.2-1~hoary1_i386.deb and during the proccess of installing it errors out saying it can't overwrite /usr/share/xscreensaver/config/electricsheep.xml...anyone tell me how to fix this?
anyone know?
where did you get that .deb from?
where did you get that .deb from? if it is not for you exact distribution then don't use it

got the deb file from http://packages.ubuntu.com/cgi-bin/download.pl?arch=i386&file=pool%2Funiverse%2Fe%2Felectricsheep%2Felectricsheep_2.6.2-1~hoary1_i386.deb&md5sum=c0b47404763b62b7b9f4cc681a64d316&arch=i386&type=main
do this, ls /usr/share/xscreensaver/config/electric* and see if you get a result
is there something there?
says no file or dir
so do this >>sudo touch /usr/share/xscreensaver/config/electricsheep.xml<< then try again - report it as a bug if that is the fix point that out :)
says same thing...
check if the file now exists - use the up arrow to go back the couple of commands to the >>ls ... << command
paste the whole output of the dpkg command to paste.ubuntulinux.nl
done
I have no further ideas, I was hoping for that to be the way
I would figure something else out
which version of ubuntu is it? what kind of modem is it?
he said it came in a hp computer
no, you do this
you identify the program that has them open and close it correctly, if you have a terminal involved you cd / to get away from the cd
in order to copy your nautilus opened a path to the CD you need to close that
there you go, there is no tcl for hoary, I have not run that version of ubuntu in about a year
you will have to install it from source, be aware that hoary is out of support come October I would get a later distro first
its for a friend...that was all the disk he had...and he is learning it while waiting on the dapper disk
I would see if it was in back-ports from breezy check you have the repos enabled from /etc/apt/sources.list
